Package: DFAmethods2
Type: Package
Title: Detrended Fluctuation Analysis and Related Methods
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(given = "Ikaro Daniel de Carvalho",
           family = "Barreto",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "daniel.carvalho.ib@gmail.com"),
    person(given = "Luiz Henrique",
           family = "Dore",
           role = "aut"))
Description: A collection of Detrended Fluctuation Analysis ('DFA') methods
    for studying long-range correlations in time series. It provides
    detrended fluctuation analysis, detrended cross-correlation analysis,
    detrended cross-correlation and partial cross-correlation coefficients,
    detrended multiple linear regression, scale-wise effect sizes, and the
    associated significance tests (Shen-Podobnik, Kristoufek and
    intersection-union). The scale-dependent standardized coefficients, the
    scale-wise effect size and the intersection-union test follow Barreto et
    al. (2021) <doi:10.1016/j.physa.2021.126259>.
